[b]Commodity Heat Reversal[/b]

[b]What it does[/b]
Detects overextended, exhausted price moves in commodity futures and signals mean-reversion entries back toward the EMA20. A dual heat score independently evaluates long and short setups across five evidence components; a signal fires when the score crosses a threshold and the closing bar confirms the direction.

[b]Heat Score Components (0–7 points)[/b]
[list]
[*][b]ATR Distance (2 pts)[/b] — price is extended more than 2.5× ATR14 beyond EMA50
[*][b]ATR Expansion (2 pts)[/b] — current ATR14 exceeds the 50-bar average by 1.5× (momentum behind the move)
[*][b]RSI Extreme (1 pt)[/b] — RSI above 72 (short) or below 28 (long)
[*][b]Wick Pressure (1 pt)[/b] — rejection wick occupies more than 35% of the bar's range
[*][b]Bollinger Band Breach (1 pt)[/b] — close outside the 2σ band
[/list]

[b]Signal Logic[/b]
[list]
[*]Score ≥ threshold (default 5/7) + confirmation (close beyond prior bar range or EMA9)
[*]Optional EMA200 trend filter — with an extreme-score override for high-conviction counter-trend setups
[/list]

[b]Visualization[/b]
[list]
[*]EMA20 / EMA50 / EMA200 plotted on chart
[*]Signal markers (▲ LONG / ▼ SHORT) with SL and TP level lines on signal bars
[*]Score dashboard table — live scores, active signal, trend direction, RSI
[/list]

[b]Parameters[/b]
[list]
[*][b]Score Threshold[/b] — minimum score to trigger (1–7, default 5)
[*][b]Extreme Score Threshold[/b] — counter-trend override threshold (default 6)
[*][b]ATR Distance Mult[/b] — how far from EMA50 counts as extended (default 2.5)
[*][b]ATR Expansion Mult[/b] — volatility expansion multiplier (default 1.5)
[*][b]SL ATR Multiplier[/b] — stop distance beyond the swing high/low (default 1.2)
[/list]

